The paper deals with information dissemination in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses network connectivity and communication, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of randomized algorithms and the analysis of lower bounds suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
